Interface IScmEvents

      • EXTENSION_PROPERTY_NAME

        static final java.lang.String EXTENSION_PROPERTY_NAME
        Change event extension constant used in baseline, snapshot, stream or change set events which indicates a property has been changed. Valid values include:
        • IWorkspace.NAME_PROPERTY
        • IWorkspace.DESCRIPTION_PROPERTY
        • IWorkspace.OWNER_PROPERTY
        • IWorkspace.VISIBILITY_PROPERTY
        • Workspace.FLOWS_PROPERTY
        • IBaseline.NAME_PROPERTY
        • IBaseline.COMMENT_PROPERTY
        • IBaselineSet.NAME_PROPERTY
        • IBaselineSet.COMMENT_PROPERTY
        • IChangeSet.COMMENT_PROPERTY
        • IChangeSet.SOURCE_PROPERTY

        Since:
        0.12.0.2 (RTC 7.0.2)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTENSION_PROPERTY_PATTERN

        static final java.lang.String EXTENSION_PROPERTY_PATTERN
        Change event extension pattern used to provide property values for the changed item or some other item related to the changed item. The pattern should be fill with the item type and property name. example: A new component event may indicate the item id of the initial change set: NLS.bind(IScmEvents.EXTENSION_PROPERTY_PATTERN, IChangeSet.ITEM_TYPE.getName(), IChangeSet.ITEM_ID_PROPERTY) The completed pattern must be less than 250 bytes.
        Since:
        0.12.0.2 (RTC 7.0.2)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        Change event string extension constant used to indicate changes in read permissions. Set in conjunction with #EXTENSION_READ_PERMISSION_MODE. This represents the new permission context, in which the valid values are one of:
